Package: pinba-engine-common
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Pinba storage engine for MySQL and MariaDB — common files
 Pinba is a storage engine for MySQL and MariaDB that collects and processes
 application runtime statistics sent over UDP by Pinba clients, most commonly
 the Pinba PHP extension. It provides real-time, per-request performance
 monitoring and profiling, queried through ordinary SQL, without any additional
 infrastructure.
 .
 This package contains shared data files: the SQL schema for the default tables,
 the hostname-width upgrade SQL script for existing installations, and
 documentation.

Package: pinba-engine-mysql-8.0
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, pinba-engine-common,
 mysql-server (>= 8.0~), mysql-server (<< 8.1~)
Conflicts: pinba-engine-mysql-8.4, pinba-engine-mariadb-10.11, pinba-engine-mariadb-11.8
Replaces: pinba-engine-mysql-8.4
Description: Pinba storage engine plugin for MySQL 8.0
 Pinba collects and processes application runtime statistics sent over UDP by
 Pinba clients, most commonly the Pinba PHP extension, and exposes them through
 ordinary SQL as real-time reports for performance monitoring and profiling.
 .
 This package contains ha_pinba.so compiled against MySQL 8.0 server headers.
 Install this package if you run MySQL 8.0.
 .
 After installation, activate the plugin in MySQL:
   INSTALL PLUGIN pinba SONAME 'ha_pinba.so';
 Then create the default tables:
   SOURCE /usr/share/pinba_engine/default_tables.sql

