Package: pinba-engine-mariadb-10.11
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, pinba-engine-common,
 mariadb-server (>= 1:10.11), mariadb-server (<< 1:10.12)
Conflicts: pinba-engine-mysql-8.0, pinba-engine-mysql-8.4, pinba-engine-mariadb-11.8
Description: Pinba storage engine plugin for MariaDB 10.11
 Pinba collects and processes application runtime statistics sent over UDP by
 Pinba clients, most commonly the Pinba PHP extension, and exposes them through
 ordinary SQL as real-time reports for performance monitoring and profiling.
 .
 This package contains ha_pinba.so compiled against MariaDB 10.11 server
 headers. Install this package if you run MariaDB 10.11 (the default on
 Ubuntu 24.04 LTS). The storage engine plugin is ABI-bound to the server's
 major.minor series, so it conflicts with the MySQL and other MariaDB plugin
 packages — install exactly the one matching your database server.
 .
 After installation, activate the plugin in MariaDB:
   INSTALL PLUGIN pinba SONAME 'ha_pinba.so';
 Then create the default tables:
   SOURCE /usr/share/pinba_engine/default_tables.sql

